{"type":"message","id":"ec265559","parentId":"e97c652d","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:37:43.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Initial Findings**\n\nI've made some progress. The initial call to the docs page was pretty thin, looking more like a placeholder. A follow-up attempt to access the API docs then failed with a 404, which is interesting.\n\n\n**Examining Documentation Approach**\n\nThe sparse content retrieved from the first call to `docs.waxpeer.com` leads me to believe the documentation relies heavily on JavaScript. My next step involves using the browser tool to navigate the URL and capture a snapshot. This way, I should obtain the complete, rendered content including the important \"P2P,\" \"extension,\" and \"rate limits\" details.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"browser_1771155463963_428","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"open","url":"https://docs.waxpeer.com/"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":6917,"output":227,"cacheRead":5157,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7144,"cost":{"input":0.013833999999999999,"output":0.002724,"cacheRead":0.0010314,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017589399999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771155455303}}
